  "description": [
    "WOULD HAVE ITALY SELECTEMIGRANTS Mussolini Says Nation Has Machinery to Comb Out Un desirables From Lists By Uif Associated Press ROME August 18On he initia tive of a group of American news paper correspondents Premier Mus solini yesterday authorized his chief of cabinet Marquis Paulucoi to issue a statement outlining the Italian gov ernments views concerning emigra tion to the United States This was the first time the government had made any official expression on the new policy of the United States with regard to immigration The Italian government says the statement does not claim the right to discuss immigration laws which constitute an Internal affair of the state which adopts them nor does it pretend to give advice to the Ameri can people who are the best judges of their own interests and unques tionably have the right to take all measures they deem necessary for national economy Will Welcome Study But the Italian government nat urally will he pleased at an Initiative which tlie American Government might wish to make at an opportune moment with the aim of studying or discussing the best practical method for reconciling the interests of the two countries The immigration policy pursued by"
